## Commands

```bash
cd backend && pytest            # Backend contract + integration tests (FakeGCPProvider — no cloud calls)
cd frontend && pytest           # Frontend integration tests
cd backend && ruff check .      # Lint backend
cd frontend && ruff check .     # Lint frontend
cd backend && uvicorn src.main:app --reload   # Run backend dev server
cd frontend && streamlit run src/app.py       # Run frontend dev server

# Opt-in manifest validation against a real Kubernetes API server using server-side dry-run.
# Requires a scratch kubeconfig; NEVER creates real resources (dry_run=["All"]).
LLMOPS_K8S_DRYRUN_KUBECONFIG=~/.kube/scratch-config \
  cd backend && pytest tests/dryrun
```

## Code Style

Python 3.11: Follow standard conventions. Ruff for linting.

## Recent Changes
- 008-gpu-cpu-deploy: Added GPU/CPU hardware selector for public model deployment. GPU path uses Lightning AI managed cloud (LitServe+vLLM); CPU path unchanged (GKE Autopilot + TGI-CPU). New ⚡ Lightning AI credentials tab. `deployments` table extended with `hardware_type` and `lightning_ai_deployment_id`; GKE columns made nullable.
- 007-gke-inference-pipeline: Added real GKE Autopilot deployment pipeline, GCP credential management, deployment orchestrator, status polling loop, and inference proxy.
- 006-session-persistence: Added backend-managed platform sessions, restore/logout endpoints, and idempotent upload/deploy retries.
- 005-folder-upload-repo-deploy: Added directory upload, per-folder error isolation, public repo metadata fetch, and public repo mock deployment.

